name: **Illaunnanoon**
description: Illaunnanoon Q605-198 Sheet 71 Just off the mainland coast, W of Scraggane Pier, this is a rocky outcrop with grass growing on top. A reef extends SW which is exposed at LW, and landing is possible on the S and SE sides. There is no water and this is not a place to go camping. There is interesting life in the exposed rock pools. Birds, grass, and rock. The shallow ground to the S near the mainland shore is actually walkable at LW. Navigate with care.
